      "role": "user",
      "content": "interesting. so for Defendant B, you're saying the housing and job instability basically act as aggravating factors that increase his risk? how much weight would a judge typically give to that \"instability\" compared to the actual crime committed? would it lead to a longer sentence than Defendant A?",
